Library Lisp:dired-isearch.el lets you isearch in DiredMode matching only file names.

Recommended keybindings:

    (define-key dired-mode-map (kbd "C-s") 'dired-isearch-forward)
    (define-key dired-mode-map (kbd "C-r") 'dired-isearch-backward)
    (define-key dired-mode-map (kbd "ESC C-s") 'dired-isearch-forward-regexp)
    (define-key dired-mode-map (kbd "ESC C-r") 'dired-isearch-backward-regexp)

Download: Lisp:dired-isearch.el.


[new:DrewAdams:2006-08-20 19:44 UTC]
Another way to find only file (and directory) names in DiredMode: Hide everything but the file names, using `dired-details-toggle' (in Lisp:dired-details+.el). When the details are hidden, search doesn't find them. -- DrewAdams

